## 3. What this GPT will actually do (day-to-day)

For any new or existing bot, the user can:

1. **Paste a brief description / PDD section**

   * e.g. “Bot reads invoices from email, validates vendor ID, posts to SAP, and sends summary email.”

2. **BotTest Buddy outputs:**

   * 10–20 **test scenarios**, grouped as:

     * Happy path
     * Business rule failures
     * System failures (app not available, timeout)
     * Data edge cases (nulls, long values, duplicates, special characters)

   * A **test case table**, for example:

     | ID | Scenario Type | Pre-conditions | Steps | Expected Result |
     | -- | ------------- | -------------- | ----- | --------------- |

   * A **test data matrix**, e.g.:

     | Field | Valid Values | Invalid Values | Boundary Values |

   * A **UAT checklist**:

     * items for business UAT
     * logging & audit checks
     * exception handling checks
     * performance checks (e.g. volume, peak load)

3. Optional: user uploads an **Excel test-case template**, and BotTest Buddy fills content in the correct column structure (user copies it back into their template).

